[07:54.63] My stern effects: then what I have to do
[07:57.31] Will want true colour; tears perchance for blood.
[08:00.59]QUEEN GERTRUDE To whom do you speak this?
[08:03.52]HAMLET Do you see nothing there?
[08:05.56]QUEEN GERTRUDE Nothing at all; yet all that is I see.
[08:08.80]HAMLET Nor did you nothing hear?
[08:10.05]QUEEN GERTRUDE No, nothing but ourselves.
[08:13.21]HAMLET Why, look you there! look, how it steals away!
[08:19.28] My father, in his habit as he lived!
[08:22.70] Look, where he goes, even now, out at the portal!
[08:25.57] [Exit Ghost]
[08:26.75]QUEEN GERTRUDE This the very coinage of your brain:
[08:30.23] This bodiless creation ecstasy
[08:33.94] Is very cunning in.
[08:35.57]HAMLET Ecstasy!
[08:37.00] My pulse, as yours, doth temperately keep time,
[08:41.03] And makes as healthful music: it is not madness
[08:44.21] That I have utter'd: bring me to the test,
[08:46.81] And I the matter will re-word; which madness
[08:48.92] Would gambol from. Mother, for love of grace,
[08:52.28] Lay not that mattering unction to your soul,
