[08:59.98] Whilst rank corruption, mining all within,
[09:02.34] Infects unseen. Confess yourself to heaven;
[09:07.31] Repent what's past; avoid what is to come;
[09:10.85] And do not spread the compost on the weeds,
[09:13.14] To make them ranker. Forgive me this my virtue;
[09:16.74] For in the fatness of these pursy times
[09:19.98] Virtue itself of vice must pardon beg,
[09:22.70] Yea, curb and woo for leave to do him good.
